import { useNavigation } from "@react-navigation/native"
import { Image, Pressable, Text, TextInput, View } from "react-native"

const Home = () => {
    const nav = useNavigation()
    return(
        <View>
            <View style={{alignItems:'center'}}>
                <Image style={{width:271,height:271}} source={require('../assets/Image 95.png')} />
            </View>
            <View style={{alignItems:'center'}}>
                <Text style={{color:'purple',fontSize:24,fontWeight:'bold'}}>
                    MANAGE YOUR TASK
                </Text>
            </View>
            <View style={{width:334,height:43,alignItems:'center',flexDirection:"row",borderWidth:1,borderRadius:10,marginLeft: 25}}>
                <Image style={{width:20,height:20}} source={require('../assets/gmail.png')}/>
                <TextInput  placeholder="enter your name"/>
            </View>
            <Pressable onPress={()=>nav.navigate('view1')}>
                <View style={{width:190,height:44}}>
                    <Text>GET STARTED</Text>
                </View>
            </Pressable>
        </View>
    )
}
export default Home
